{{!-- Generalized from tristons-loot-generator templates/history.hbs (whole file, 46 lines) and
    templates/table-manager.hbs:1-9 (Triston's Loot Generator/) — minimal PARTS.body markup for a
    standalone ApplicationV2 window (no tab-wrapper root; unlike the sheet-extension overlay this
    preset is not mounting into an existing dnd5e sheet, so there's no `tab.cssClass`/`tab.id`/
    `tab.group` container contract to honor).

    TWO KINDS OF `{{...}}` TOKEN IN THIS FILE — same convention as
    templates/sheet-extension/templates/{{TAB_ID}}.hbs (read that file's header first if this is
    your first overlay):

    1. SCAFFOLDER PLACEHOLDERS — plain-text find/replace tokens, substituted ONCE at scaffold
       time, gone from the final file. Written ALL_CAPS_WITH_UNDERSCORES, no leading/trailing
       space inside the braces: `twm-control`, `twm`, `TWM`,
       `twmPing`. This filename itself is one: `twm-control.hbs` gets renamed to
       e.g. `my-app.hbs`.

    2. RUNTIME HANDLEBARS EXPRESSIONS — real Handlebars, evaluated every time this app renders,
       sourced from `world-map-control.mjs`'s `_prepareContext()` return value. Written
       lowercase, no underscores: `{{ title }}`, `{{ exampleValue }}`. These are NOT scaffolder
       placeholders and must survive substitution untouched — a plain-text find/replace of
       ALL_CAPS_WITH_UNDERSCORES tokens cannot accidentally touch them (different case/shape),
       but keep the distinction in mind if you hand-edit this file post-scaffold.

    Verify after substitution the same way as the sheet-extension overlay:
    `grep -F "{{ title }}" <substituted-file>` and `grep -F "{{ exampleValue }}" <substituted-file>`
    must still find a match. --}}
<section class="twm-body">
  <header class="twm-header">
    <h2>{{ title }}</h2>
  </header>

  <div class="twm-content">
    <p>{{localize "TWM.twm-control.Count"}}: {{ exampleValue }}</p>
    <button type="button" data-action="twmPing">
      <i class="fas fa-map-location-dot"></i> {{localize "TWM.twm-control.ExampleAction"}}
    </button>
  </div>
</section>
